event.title: 1887, Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway built

data.event: In 1887, Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway built a branch line from Neva (3 miles west of Strong City) through Manchester to Superior, Nebraska.

event.title: 1996, the Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway merged

data.event: In 1996, the Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway merged with Burlington Northern Railroad and renamed to the current BNSF Railway.
Manchester was originally called Keystone, and under the latter name laid out in 1887.
The name Manchester was adopted by 1890.
The post office in Manchester was discontinued in 1993.
